00:08:46.490 --> 00:08:50.482
Because if you go into a meeting, right?

132
00:08:50.482 --> 00:08:55.796
Let's say you're the CEO of the company,
and you turn around to me and

133
00:08:55.796 --> 00:09:00.858
you say, we need that element above
the fold, nobody will see it.

134
00:09:00.858 --> 00:09:06.418
And even if I come back to you with this
great argument that's all well structured

135
00:09:06.418 --> 00:09:11.184
and rest of it, it's become about
authority at this point, right?

136
00:09:11.184 --> 00:09:14.304
I've basically made you look small,
all right?

137
00:09:14.304 --> 00:09:18.102
And I've proved to the rest of
the room that you're wrong, okay?

138
00:09:18.102 --> 00:09:22.894
But there's no way, you're the CEO of the
company, there's no way you're gonna roll

139
00:09:22.894 --> 00:09:26.549
over and let me bulldoze you like that so
you're gonna fight back.

140
00:09:26.549 --> 00:09:30.560
However, if I sat down before
that meeting, and identified,

141
00:09:30.560 --> 00:09:34.435
bet the CEO is gonna say that
thing needs to be above the fold.

