156
00:10:29.353 --> 00:10:32.161
Anyway, so, common objections.

157
00:10:32.161 --> 00:10:37.369
The other thing that I do, is I try and
speak to all the stakeholders

158
00:10:37.369 --> 00:10:42.765
before I do the presentation and
I try to speak to them individually.

159
00:10:42.765 --> 00:10:47.022
This isn't always possible but it really
is worth doing if you possibly can.

160
00:10:47.022 --> 00:10:50.592
So let's say you've got a presentation
where you know you're gonna be presenting

161
00:10:50.592 --> 00:10:52.326
the design to a group of people, I try and

162
00:10:52.326 --> 00:10:55.160
talk to each of those people
individually beforehand.

163
00:10:55.160 --> 00:11:00.583
And the reason is, is that when I speak
to stakeholders individually, allows

164
00:11:00.583 --> 00:11:06.760
me to tailor my message to the things that
I know will resonate with them, right?

165
00:11:06.760 --> 00:11:10.200
So let's give you some examples.

166
00:11:10.200 --> 00:11:14.695
So if I'm speaking to a marketing person
and I'm talking about the design that I've

